inputs.description: A collection of arguments for invoking getBucketObjects.

bucket.description: Lists object keys in this S3 bucket. Alternatively, an [S3 access point](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/using-access-points.html) ARN can be specified
bucket.deprecationMessage: Use the aws_s3_objects data source instead

delimiter.description: Character used to group keys (Default: none)

encodingType.description: Encodes keys using this method (Default: none; besides none, only "url" can be used)

fetchOwner.description: Boolean specifying whether to populate the owner list (Default: false)

prefix.description: Limits results to object keys with this prefix (Default: none)

startAfter.description: Returns key names lexicographically after a specific object key in your bucket (Default: none; S3 lists object keys in UTF-8 character encoding in lexicographical order)

outputs.description: A collection of values returned by getBucketObjects.

bucket.deprecationMessage: Use the aws_s3_objects data source instead

commonPrefixes.description: List of any keys between `prefix` and the next occurrence of `delimiter` (i.e., similar to subdirectories of the `prefix` "directory"); the list is only returned when you specify `delimiter`

id.description: The provider-assigned unique ID for this managed resource.

keys.description: List of strings representing object keys

owners.description: List of strings representing object owner IDs (see `fetch_owner` above)
